      • queryParser

        public java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,LanguageEntry> queryParser(int k,
                                                                  java.lang.String file)
        Takes in an Integer representing a kmer and a String representing a file location. Reads the file in line by line and trims. Adds this to a temporary ArrayList. Checks if the kmer exists already and if so adds a 1 to the HashCode of the kmer else it creates a new HashCode. Parses the queryFile into a new map and calls on the sort method. This creates another map containing the frequencies, kmers and ranks of the languages.
        Parameters:
        k - - An Integer representing a kmer.
        file - - A String representing a file location.
        Returns:
        queryFile
